The paper is about a new method for filter diversification for face recognition, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of principal component analysis (PCA) and independent component analysis (ICA) filters, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of histogram pooling, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, and cs.IT.
